law.text:
As used in KRS 158.181 to 158.187, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Establishment clause" means the portion of the First Amendment to the United States Constitution that forbids laws respecting an establishment of religion;
"Free exercise clause" means the portion of the First Amendment to the United States Constitution that forbids laws prohibiting the free exercise of religion;
"Free speech clause" means the portion of the First Amendment to the United States Constitution that forbids laws abridging the freedom of speech;
"Public school" means any school that is operated by the state, a political subdivision of the state, or a governmental agency within the state; and
"Student" means an individual attending a public school.
